gomodel:SYNGO_2964  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.2: \"OCT2 is predominantly localized in cholinergic neurons and terminals adjacent to the perikarya of motoneurons in the anterior horn of the rat spinal cord\"\n\nFig.3: \"Localization of OCT2 on SVs at the C-terminal of a cholinergic neuron\"\n- \"Surprisingly, our results demonstrated that OCT2 was preferentially localized on SVs (Fig. 3A), although signals could be occasionally seen on the presynaptic membrane.\"\n\nFig.4: \"Localization of OCT2 on SVs in cholinergic presynaptic terminals at NMJs\"\n\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: - \"Immunoelectron microscopy: Rats were anesthetized by intraperitoneal i...\"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099056 replaced by GO:0042734" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
